# Firebase Setup Instructions

## Prerequisites
- Create a Firebase account at [https://console.firebase.google.com/](https://console.firebase.google.com/)
- Have Node.js and npm installed

## Configuration Steps
1. Create a new Firebase project in the Firebase Console

2. Go to Project Settings
   - Click on the gear icon next to "Project Overview"
   - Navigate to the "Your apps" section

3. Add a new Web App
   - Click on the "</>" icon to add a new web app
   - Register the app with a nickname (e.g., "Sulla")
   - Click "Register app"

4. Copy Firebase Configuration
   - You'll see a configuration object with your app's specific keys
   - Copy these values into the `.env` file in the project root

5. Enable Authentication Methods
   - In Firebase Console, go to "Authentication"
   - Enable "Email/Password" sign-in method

6. Set Up Firestore Database
   - Go to "Firestore Database" in the Firebase Console
   - Create a database in test mode

## Environment Variables
Replace the placeholders in `.env` with your actual Firebase project values:
- `REACT_APP_FIREBASE_API_KEY`
- `REACT_APP_FIREBASE_AUTH_DOMAIN`
- `REACT_APP_FIREBASE_PROJECT_ID`
- `REACT_APP_FIREBASE_STORAGE_BUCKET`
- `REACT_APP_FIREBASE_MESSAGING_SENDER_ID`
- `REACT_APP_FIREBASE_APP_ID`

## Installation
```bash
npm install firebase react-firebase-hooks
```

## Security Notes
- Never commit your `.env` file to version control
- Add `.env` to your `.gitignore`

## Troubleshooting
- Ensure all environment variables are correctly set
- Check Firebase Console for any configuration issues
- Verify that your IP is allowed in Firebase Authentication settings
